description:
  We prove that, for a suitable choice of real numbers $a, b$, every operator
from $\ell_2$ to $X_{a,b}$ and from $X_{a,b}$ to $\ell_2$ must be compact,
where $X_{a,b}$ is the Bourgain- Delbaen's space.

  We present an Isabelle/HOL formalization of a characterization of confluence
for quasi-reductive strongly deterministic conditional term rewrite systems,
due to Avenhaus and Lor\'ia-S\'aenz.
